parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat belt retractor can lead to the seat belt being unable to properly restrain the driver in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract
the seat belt extends to its full extent and is unable to be secured
strange noises (such as a "popping" or "rapidly closing" sound) when attempting to latch or unlatch the seat belt
the seat belt requires multiple attempts to engage
the seat belt sticks or stops midway with a noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the vehicle to lock up, lose power, and become difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: the back end of the vehicle comes around while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to slip gears, lose power, and become difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips from one gear to another
the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to properly address recall issues can lead to continued problems with the vehicle, including transfer case and transmission failures, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has been repaired for recall issues
the dealer refuses to refund repair costs
the vehicle is not properly inspected for recall issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, including valve damage, and potentially lead to costly repairs or even engine failure.
symptoms: the timing belt breaks or fails

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, engine damage, and potentially cause engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle burns excessive amounts of oil

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, become difficult to shift, or even leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the harmonic balancer can cause engine vibration, noise, and potentially lead to engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Component Failure (Fuel Line, Ignition Wires, Coil, Wire Harness)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine components can cause engine failure, stalling, or even fires.
symptoms: Smoke comes from under the hood
a small fire occurs around the fuel line
